1
00:00:04,742 --> 00:00:06,544
Can you really restore
something like that?

2
00:00:07,112 --> 00:00:08,446
We have no choice but to try.

3
00:00:08,513 --> 00:00:10,748
<i>Because Tsuda's notebook is inside this.</i>

4
00:00:13,918 --> 00:00:15,320
Now we have Tsuda's notebook…

5
00:00:15,386 --> 00:00:18,923
We should be able to find out
what happened 30 years ago.

6
00:00:24,362 --> 00:00:28,166
<i>"March 21, 1995.</i>

7
00:00:28,766 --> 00:00:31,236
<i>I tailed Amagi of the Igarashi-gumi…</i>

8
00:00:37,842 --> 00:00:40,145
<i>and found their drug hand-off spot."</i>

9
00:00:40,211 --> 00:00:41,379
Yes.

10
00:00:41,446 --> 00:00:43,882
The Karashima factory is making our tools.

11
00:00:44,449 --> 00:00:45,717
<i>"Tools.</i>

12
00:00:45,783 --> 00:00:46,851
<i>Karashima.</i>

13
00:00:47,452 --> 00:00:48,953
<i>Is it slang for guns?</i>

14
00:00:49,954 --> 00:00:51,723
<i>I'll refocus my investigation.</i>

15
00:00:52,924 --> 00:00:54,559
<i>April 13.</i>

16
00:00:55,426 --> 00:00:56,761
<i>There were two men.</i>

17
00:00:57,262 --> 00:01:00,165
<i>Amagi and another man I can't identify.</i>

18
00:01:00,965 --> 00:01:03,701
<i>A gun transaction took place.</i>

19
00:01:04,669 --> 00:01:07,272
<i>Compensation was handed out</i>
<i>to those involved.</i>

20
00:01:08,306 --> 00:01:10,375
<i>10:28 p.m.</i>

21
00:01:11,142 --> 00:01:13,978
<i>Tagusari headed to the factory</i>
<i>carrying something.</i>

22
00:01:14,846 --> 00:01:17,815
<i>Is Tagusari, a factory employee,</i>
<i>also involved in this?</i>

23
00:01:22,754 --> 00:01:26,824
<i>April 26, 1995."</i>

24
00:01:27,458 --> 00:01:28,426
Mr. Tagusari.

25
00:01:28,493 --> 00:01:32,030
-Do you have a moment?
-You again? So persistent.

26
00:01:32,096 --> 00:01:35,033
They won't print my novel
without your testimony.

27
00:01:35,099 --> 00:01:36,668
I don't care about that!

28
00:01:40,071 --> 00:01:44,175
<i>"However, due to a fire at the factory,</i>
<i>my investigation was cut short.</i>

29
00:01:44,242 --> 00:01:47,245
<i>Left with no choice,</i>
<i>I changed my pitch back to drugs…</i>

30
00:01:48,379 --> 00:01:51,416
and I succeeded
in stealing their drug client list."

31
00:01:52,650 --> 00:01:56,588
Then, Tsuda was pursued
by the Igarashi-gumi and went missing?

32
00:01:57,155 --> 00:01:59,357
And he mentioned "another man."

33
00:01:59,424 --> 00:02:01,960
Who did the Igarashi-gumi
hand the money to?

34
00:02:04,195 --> 00:02:07,832
"However, the darkness surrounding
the illicit manufacturing runs deep.

35
00:02:07,899 --> 00:02:11,135
The involved parties include
the Karashima Metal Factory,

36
00:02:11,202 --> 00:02:12,537
the Igarashi-gumi,

37
00:02:12,604 --> 00:02:13,705
and beyond that…"

38
00:02:20,245 --> 00:02:21,212
<i>Yes?</i>

39
00:02:22,380 --> 00:02:24,616
Sorry for coming all the way
to your house.

40
00:02:26,284 --> 00:02:27,752
<i>Did something happen?</i>

41
00:02:28,987 --> 00:02:31,589
There's just something I want to check.

42
00:02:33,558 --> 00:02:37,161
Show me what you guys took.

43
00:02:43,568 --> 00:02:44,535
Hey.

44
00:02:45,036 --> 00:02:46,337
What do you mean?

45
00:02:47,238 --> 00:02:48,439
Excuse me.

46
00:02:49,707 --> 00:02:50,875
Mr. Koike…

47
00:02:56,514 --> 00:02:58,082
The older brother

48
00:02:58,850 --> 00:03:01,819
was looking into
the Igarashi-gumi shootings.

49
00:03:02,353 --> 00:03:07,025
Right after that, the younger brother
gave us false info for a raid.

50
00:03:08,660 --> 00:03:11,429
How can I not suspect you two?

51
00:03:14,265 --> 00:03:19,404
The cleaners said
two men came to visit them.

52
00:03:21,506 --> 00:03:22,540
Hand it over.

53
00:03:23,975 --> 00:03:24,976
Hand it over!

54
00:03:31,482 --> 00:03:32,350
We don't have it.

55
00:03:33,951 --> 00:03:36,254
The information was irrelevant.
I threw it away.

56
00:03:36,321 --> 00:03:38,256
Must be at the disposal plant now.

57
00:03:40,391 --> 00:03:41,592
Mind if I…

58
00:03:43,561 --> 00:03:44,696
take a look around?

59
00:03:44,762 --> 00:03:45,730
Go ahead.

60
00:03:51,669 --> 00:03:55,707
Taking evidence constitutes theft
under Article 235 of the Penal Code.

61
00:03:56,274 --> 00:03:58,676
In addition, it involves
breach of discipline,

62
00:03:58,743 --> 00:04:00,812
destruction of evidence,

63
00:04:01,813 --> 00:04:03,181
and abuse of authority.

64
00:04:04,916 --> 00:04:09,120
For now, should I pass this along
to internal affairs?

65
00:04:13,825 --> 00:04:16,561
<i>This is Sakai, Kanagawa</i>
<i>Prefectural Police Headquarters.</i>

66
00:04:18,262 --> 00:04:19,263
<i>Hello?</i>

67
00:04:20,431 --> 00:04:21,499
<i>Hello?</i>

68
00:04:22,367 --> 00:04:23,301
<i>Hello?</i>

69
00:04:23,368 --> 00:04:24,435
I told you.

70
00:04:24,502 --> 00:04:25,670
<i>-Hello?</i>
-There's nothing here.

71
00:04:25,737 --> 00:04:26,838
It’s in the microwave.

72
00:04:50,328 --> 00:04:51,562
What about your computer?

73
00:04:52,130 --> 00:04:53,364
There's data on it, no?

74
00:04:58,603 --> 00:04:59,437
Right here.

75
00:05:14,018 --> 00:05:15,319
That case…

76
00:05:18,055 --> 00:05:19,624
its statute already expired.

77
00:05:26,364 --> 00:05:27,799
Don't let me catch you again.

78
00:05:49,854 --> 00:05:50,755
Hello, sir.

79
00:05:50,822 --> 00:05:52,256
Hello, sir.

80
00:05:55,760 --> 00:05:56,761
Mr. Koike,

81
00:05:56,828 --> 00:06:00,131
the First Division is asking for backup
on the Sagamihara murder case.

82
00:06:00,198 --> 00:06:01,399
Okay.

83
00:06:11,609 --> 00:06:13,344
Tagusari, I’ll leave the rest to you.

84
00:06:17,548 --> 00:06:21,219
YOMOGIDA-CHO FAMILY MURDER CASE,
PARENTS KILLED, BROTHERS IN FOSTER CARE

85
00:06:26,524 --> 00:06:27,725
Oh, Ms. Kudo.

86
00:06:28,292 --> 00:06:29,126
What’s up?

87
00:06:29,193 --> 00:06:32,663
Yesterday, I was drinking with a peer,
and we ended up talking about Mr. Koike.

88
00:06:33,431 --> 00:06:36,400
He used to be in the Prefectural Police's
First Division, right?

89
00:06:36,934 --> 00:06:38,870
That was a long time ago.

90
00:06:39,737 --> 00:06:41,305
Don't you think it's strange?

91
00:06:43,140 --> 00:06:45,977
He's elite, yet he has been stuck
at this local station.

92
00:06:46,611 --> 00:06:49,347
-Maybe he's not interested in a promotion.
-It's just that…

93
00:06:50,014 --> 00:06:51,983
I heard a slightly concerning rumor.

94
00:06:53,618 --> 00:06:55,620
Apparently, his old partner

95
00:06:55,686 --> 00:06:58,322
was dishonorably discharged
for leaking information.

96
00:06:59,924 --> 00:07:01,592
Dishonorably discharged?

97
00:07:02,093 --> 00:07:07,298
Could it be that Mr. Koike can't return
to First Division because of that partner?

98
00:07:19,143 --> 00:07:20,845
<i>You really want…</i>

99
00:07:20,912 --> 00:07:23,714
to protect those brothers, huh?

100
00:07:36,561 --> 00:07:37,562
You still open?

101
00:07:38,162 --> 00:07:39,163
Yes.

102
00:07:45,670 --> 00:07:47,104
You working here today?

103
00:07:47,171 --> 00:07:48,973
Today, I'm meeting up with Makoto.

104
00:07:53,044 --> 00:07:54,111
By the way…

105
00:07:54,745 --> 00:07:57,848
Did you finish
putting together the shredded paper?

106
00:07:58,816 --> 00:07:59,750
Yes.

107
00:08:01,052 --> 00:08:02,086
For the most part.

108
00:08:04,889 --> 00:08:05,890
Did something happen?

109
00:08:08,693 --> 00:08:11,262
-Sorry, I'm late.
-I just got here too.

110
00:08:12,330 --> 00:08:14,599
-Mogi, fried rice and gyoza.
<i>-Chukadon </i>for me.

111
00:08:15,466 --> 00:08:16,701
Coming right up.

112
00:08:20,338 --> 00:08:21,706
How's Mr. Koike?

113
00:08:23,608 --> 00:08:26,043
Just working normally, as usual.

114
00:08:27,845 --> 00:08:29,313
What do we do next?

115
00:08:29,380 --> 00:08:32,116
The gun trade involved
the factory manager,

116
00:08:32,750 --> 00:08:36,053
Amagi of the Igarashi-gumi,
and another man.

117
00:08:36,887 --> 00:08:39,323
Plus, it's highly likely
our old man was involved.

118
00:08:39,390 --> 00:08:40,992
I know.

119
00:08:41,058 --> 00:08:43,394
Tsuda’s notebook was our only lead.

120
00:08:43,461 --> 00:08:45,630
Then why did you
hand it over to Mr. Koike?

121
00:08:45,696 --> 00:08:48,199
If they put us under surveillance,
we won't get to act.

122
00:08:51,769 --> 00:08:53,070
Did you hand it over?

123
00:08:59,110 --> 00:09:00,511
We give up.

124
00:09:01,012 --> 00:09:03,147
Old man, get a job!

125
00:09:17,595 --> 00:09:19,330
Are you playing for money?

126
00:09:21,632 --> 00:09:23,501
It’s getting good. Don't interrupt us.

127
00:09:23,567 --> 00:09:25,803
You want to go to jail at your age?

128
00:09:38,783 --> 00:09:40,651
He also visited here recently.

129
00:09:41,819 --> 00:09:43,087
Mr. Koike did?

130
00:09:43,888 --> 00:09:46,924
He seems desperate to stop you and Minoru.

131
00:09:49,460 --> 00:09:51,796
It's because he couldn't do
anything back then.

132
00:09:54,365 --> 00:09:56,000
What an unnecessary atonement.

133
00:09:57,134 --> 00:09:59,003
Maybe that's not the only reason.

134
00:10:02,840 --> 00:10:04,075
It's no use.

135
00:10:05,309 --> 00:10:06,877
You're already in check.

136
00:10:06,944 --> 00:10:08,012
What?

137
00:10:08,079 --> 00:10:09,346
Wait, really?

138
00:10:09,413 --> 00:10:10,314
No,

139
00:10:10,915 --> 00:10:13,551
there might still be a piece I can move.

140
00:10:31,802 --> 00:10:33,504
PERSONNEL RECORDS
TAKAHIRO SASAOKA

141
00:10:33,571 --> 00:10:34,905
Sasaoka…

142
00:10:34,972 --> 00:10:37,108
The detective
who was in charge of you guys.

143
00:10:38,609 --> 00:10:40,911
Makoto, you already understand, don't you?

144
00:10:41,946 --> 00:10:46,250
Yesterday, your mother
and father passed away.

145
00:10:46,317 --> 00:10:48,085
<i>So he is Mr. Koike's former partner.</i>

146
00:10:48,919 --> 00:10:50,855
What about this Sasaoka guy?

147
00:10:50,921 --> 00:10:52,490
I did a little digging.

148
00:10:53,824 --> 00:10:55,192
Interesting things came up.

149
00:10:56,927 --> 00:11:00,498
In 1998, Sasaoka
was dishonorably discharged

150
00:11:00,564 --> 00:11:02,066
for leaking information.

151
00:11:02,133 --> 00:11:03,634
Leaking information?

152
00:11:04,335 --> 00:11:05,469
To the Igarashi-gumi.

153
00:11:06,871 --> 00:11:09,807
Sasaoka and the Igarashi-gumi
were in collusion.

154
00:11:11,876 --> 00:11:15,112
But, how does this link
to the illegal deals at the factory?

155
00:11:15,179 --> 00:11:17,314
Where did the manufactured guns go?

156
00:11:20,417 --> 00:11:21,685
He was a smuggler.

157
00:11:21,752 --> 00:11:23,888
Before he joined the Kanagawa PD,

158
00:11:23,954 --> 00:11:26,190
Sasaoka was at
the Kawasaki Marine Police Station.

159
00:11:27,958 --> 00:11:29,093
<i>He was in an environment</i>

160
00:11:29,160 --> 00:11:32,329
<i>where he could obtain</i>
<i>the maritime patrol schedules.</i>

161
00:11:34,098 --> 00:11:37,234
<i>And he leaked the safe dates</i>
<i>and times for smuggling.</i>

162
00:11:40,738 --> 00:11:41,572
<i>Hello?</i>

163
00:11:42,773 --> 00:11:46,076
The deal is on the night
of the 13th at 11:00 p.m.

164
00:11:47,244 --> 00:11:48,479
Understood.

165
00:11:49,046 --> 00:11:50,781
We'll have them ready by then.

166
00:11:50,848 --> 00:11:53,951
<i>So the man the notebook</i>
<i>mentioned was Sasaoka.</i>

167
00:11:54,018 --> 00:11:56,754
At the same time,
Sasaoka was dishonorably discharged,

168
00:11:56,821 --> 00:11:59,423
and his partner, Mr. Koike, vanished
from the Prefectural Police.

169
00:12:00,224 --> 00:12:01,358
Why would he?

170
00:12:01,926 --> 00:12:03,527
I couldn't find out the reason.

171
00:12:04,361 --> 00:12:06,964
He was a First Division detective,
yet suddenly,

172
00:12:07,031 --> 00:12:10,100
he transferred to Traffic
at a local station, for some reason.

173
00:12:11,202 --> 00:12:12,937
The two were in on it together.

174
00:12:16,140 --> 00:12:18,776
Mr. Koike's name
might also be in Tsuda's notes.

175
00:12:21,278 --> 00:12:23,247
Was Mr. Koike part of the deals too?

176
00:12:38,963 --> 00:12:39,830
Tagusari.

177
00:12:45,302 --> 00:12:47,738
This is all we confiscated
from the Igarashi-gumi.

178
00:12:48,239 --> 00:12:50,841
Where did the information
about our raid leak from?

179
00:12:52,810 --> 00:12:54,144
No idea.

180
00:12:54,678 --> 00:12:55,980
I see.

181
00:12:57,181 --> 00:12:58,249
Hey.

182
00:12:59,016 --> 00:13:01,252
Anything else come in
from the main station?

183
00:13:04,388 --> 00:13:07,157
INTERROGATION ROOM TWO

184
00:13:10,261 --> 00:13:11,128
What's wrong?

185
00:13:11,762 --> 00:13:14,465
<i>I saw Mr. Koike</i>
<i>at the Prefectural Police earlier.</i>

186
00:13:14,999 --> 00:13:15,833
Yeah.

187
00:13:16,400 --> 00:13:19,536
He's chasing an unresolved case
from when he was in First Division.

188
00:13:20,070 --> 00:13:21,372
Did you find anything?

189
00:13:21,438 --> 00:13:22,873
<i>I checked with Organized Crime.</i>

190
00:13:22,940 --> 00:13:26,010
Mr. Koike hasn't submitted
Tsuda's notebook to them.

191
00:13:31,515 --> 00:13:32,650
Why not?

192
00:13:34,818 --> 00:13:37,988
So he was really involved
in the illicit manufacturing after all?

193
00:13:38,689 --> 00:13:41,225
But we don't have proof yet.

194
00:13:42,092 --> 00:13:43,294
I'll check on my end.

195
00:13:43,360 --> 00:13:45,696
And I'll look into Sasaoka.

196
00:13:46,196 --> 00:13:47,932
Thank you.

197
00:13:47,998 --> 00:13:52,002
CHINESE RESTAURANT
MOCCHAN

198
00:14:13,123 --> 00:14:14,158
Yukiteru.

199
00:14:14,224 --> 00:14:15,292
Mom?

200
00:14:20,264 --> 00:14:21,298
What's wrong?

201
00:14:22,399 --> 00:14:25,102
Aren't you supposed to be
working at Ms. Karashima's?

202
00:14:26,337 --> 00:14:27,938
Fumi told me

203
00:14:28,739 --> 00:14:32,776
to take some time off for a while.

204
00:14:34,445 --> 00:14:35,412
Is that so?

205
00:14:36,914 --> 00:14:40,084
Mom, just take it easy and rest for now.

206
00:14:42,553 --> 00:14:44,855
I'll make money somehow.

207
00:14:46,256 --> 00:14:48,092
Look how dependable you've become.

208
00:14:49,059 --> 00:14:50,661
What's that supposed to mean?

209
00:14:51,362 --> 00:14:54,331
I'm glad you took over that place.

210
00:14:56,467 --> 00:14:57,468
Well…

211
00:14:58,068 --> 00:15:00,604
It's not like I had any other work
I wanted to do.

212
00:15:01,839 --> 00:15:03,574
It's work you can do, right?

213
00:15:06,410 --> 00:15:08,278
Since you were a kid, Yukiteru…

214
00:15:08,946 --> 00:15:13,017
You were a bit more awkward
than everyone else.

215
00:15:14,051 --> 00:15:18,288
It used to take you an hour or two
just to do your math homework.

216
00:15:19,223 --> 00:15:20,758
That was a long time ago!

217
00:15:23,761 --> 00:15:26,697
I need to find some work too.

218
00:15:28,232 --> 00:15:30,934
Many things still worry me,
so I can't die just yet.

219
00:15:32,136 --> 00:15:34,438
Hey, don't say stupid things!

220
00:15:44,381 --> 00:15:47,017
SEND BEKO TO ANOTHER FARM?
YES / NO

221
00:15:57,261 --> 00:15:58,362
Mr. Tagusari.

222
00:15:59,196 --> 00:16:00,898
Do you have plans after this?

223
00:16:01,799 --> 00:16:02,766
What's up?

224
00:16:02,833 --> 00:16:04,401
Want to go get a drink?

225
00:16:05,335 --> 00:16:06,437
Why?

226
00:16:07,004 --> 00:16:07,938
"Why?"

227
00:16:08,505 --> 00:16:10,607
Not sure how to answer that.

228
00:16:11,742 --> 00:16:14,244
Oh, no, it's just that…

229
00:16:17,314 --> 00:16:18,515
I have an errand to run.

230
00:16:20,451 --> 00:16:21,518
Well then…

231
00:16:26,256 --> 00:16:27,091
Kudo.

232
00:16:29,693 --> 00:16:31,261
Find a place.

233
00:16:32,262 --> 00:16:33,263
What?

234
00:16:33,831 --> 00:16:34,531
Why not?

235
00:16:36,967 --> 00:16:39,369
I'll go ahead and find
an expensive place then.

236
00:16:39,903 --> 00:16:41,371
And you're paying, Mr. Tagusari.

237
00:16:41,438 --> 00:16:42,539
What?

238
00:16:42,606 --> 00:16:44,308
See you.

239
00:17:12,136 --> 00:17:13,971
You won't get it open, you know.

240
00:17:16,907 --> 00:17:19,576
You just won't give up, will you?

241
00:17:29,086 --> 00:17:31,155
I told you there won't be another chance.

242
00:17:32,389 --> 00:17:34,691
-Quit being a cop…
-We're in the same boat.

243
00:17:38,962 --> 00:17:40,564
Shall we go somewhere else?

244
00:17:49,873 --> 00:17:51,375
Hurry up and talk.

245
00:17:51,441 --> 00:17:53,177
I have Ishizaka waiting outside.

246
00:17:54,778 --> 00:17:56,813
Then I'll just cut to the chase.

247
00:17:59,016 --> 00:18:00,617
Where is Tsuda's notebook?

248
00:18:01,185 --> 00:18:02,953
Do you think I'm going to answer that?

249
00:18:03,020 --> 00:18:04,521
I think you have no choice.

250
00:18:05,689 --> 00:18:08,525
Since you took home evidence
without even submitting it.

251
00:18:13,764 --> 00:18:15,465
Mr. Sasaoka and you,

252
00:18:16,266 --> 00:18:17,968
what were you doing together?

253
00:18:20,737 --> 00:18:22,172
Mr. Koike!

254
00:18:22,239 --> 00:18:25,709
Everyone has skeletons in their closets,
don't you know that?

255
00:18:28,178 --> 00:18:31,315
Right and wrong…

256
00:18:32,082 --> 00:18:34,918
crooked and straight.

257
00:18:36,753 --> 00:18:40,924
-Everything has good and bad sides.
-Don't try to deceive me.

258
00:18:40,991 --> 00:18:42,759
I think there's one more side.

259
00:18:48,198 --> 00:18:50,100
Things you're better off not knowing.

260
00:18:58,842 --> 00:18:59,977
That notebook…

261
00:19:02,145 --> 00:19:03,380
I destroyed it.

262
00:19:13,156 --> 00:19:15,225
Did you find anything about Sasaoka?

263
00:19:16,627 --> 00:19:18,495
According to what I heard from above,

264
00:19:18,562 --> 00:19:21,164
he was also involved
in the Yomogida-cho evictions,

265
00:19:21,231 --> 00:19:23,533
carried out by the Igarashi-gumi.

266
00:19:24,134 --> 00:19:25,002
Evictions?

267
00:19:25,068 --> 00:19:28,338
He was making money from that,
as well as the illicit gun manufacturing?

268
00:19:28,405 --> 00:19:31,441
However,
they don't know anything beyond that.

269
00:19:32,075 --> 00:19:35,178
Even at headquarters, talking about
Sasaoka seems to be taboo.

270
00:19:35,712 --> 00:19:36,813
Taboo?

271
00:19:37,381 --> 00:19:40,150
Maybe there's something
they don't want dug up.

272
00:19:51,795 --> 00:19:53,096
Mr. Sasaoka.

273
00:19:57,367 --> 00:19:59,236
What is it? After all this time.

274
00:20:21,458 --> 00:20:22,326
Koike…

275
00:20:24,127 --> 00:20:25,495
That case…

276
00:20:26,530 --> 00:20:28,231
isn't over yet.

277
00:20:29,633 --> 00:20:32,636
MOCCHAN

278
00:20:33,704 --> 00:20:34,705
Closed?

279
00:20:34,771 --> 00:20:36,473
Today isn't his usual day off.

280
00:20:39,142 --> 00:20:43,080
Hey, why wasn't this whole area evicted?

281
00:20:48,452 --> 00:20:51,121
Maybe Tsuda also wrote
about the evictions.

282
00:20:52,356 --> 00:20:54,257
We have to read the rest.

283
00:21:02,733 --> 00:21:03,867
What's wrong?

284
00:22:02,426 --> 00:22:03,260
You.

285
00:22:03,827 --> 00:22:04,961
Are you the cleaner?

286
00:22:05,028 --> 00:22:07,631
This is the Igarashi-gumi's
dumping ground, isn't it?

287
00:22:14,337 --> 00:22:17,441
Are you here to take back
those paper scraps?

288
00:22:24,781 --> 00:22:29,386
If that kind of info leaks, who knows
what the Igarashi-gumi will do to me!

289
00:22:29,953 --> 00:22:30,887
"That kind of info"?

290
00:22:30,954 --> 00:22:32,522
So you read that notebook?

291
00:22:33,056 --> 00:22:34,291
Drugs…

292
00:22:34,858 --> 00:22:37,060
Fraud… Illicit gun manufacturing…

293
00:22:37,627 --> 00:22:39,996
If mishandled, those files
and that notebook

294
00:22:40,063 --> 00:22:42,065
can shake the Igarashi-gumi to its core!

295
00:22:42,632 --> 00:22:45,135
Shake what? You put it through a shredder!

296
00:22:47,103 --> 00:22:47,971
Don't tell me…

297
00:22:48,638 --> 00:22:49,973
Did you back it up as data?

298
00:22:58,782 --> 00:23:02,052
That cleaner
took photos of the entire notebook.

299
00:23:05,021 --> 00:23:07,624
The man involved in the illicit
manufacturing really is Sasaoka.

300
00:23:08,158 --> 00:23:11,228
However, Mr. Koike's name
was nowhere to be found.

301
00:23:11,761 --> 00:23:13,997
So even Tsuda
couldn't investigate that far.

302
00:23:15,665 --> 00:23:17,133
Didn't mention Dad much, either.

303
00:23:19,169 --> 00:23:21,738
"April 13, 1995.

304
00:23:22,472 --> 00:23:25,475
Factory employee, Tagusari,
transported guns to port."

305
00:23:26,209 --> 00:23:28,078
Did he really write only that?

306
00:23:29,346 --> 00:23:31,781
Seems Dad didn't say anything
when interviewed,

307
00:23:31,848 --> 00:23:33,750
and no one knows why he was involved.

308
00:23:38,622 --> 00:23:39,556
What is it?

309
00:23:43,627 --> 00:23:45,629
Do you want to know the truth that badly?

310
00:23:47,097 --> 00:23:48,765
You've asked me like a million times.

311
00:23:50,934 --> 00:23:52,469
No matter what it may be?

312
00:23:53,503 --> 00:23:55,939
You think I would hesitate
when we've gone so far?

313
00:24:11,154 --> 00:24:14,491
On April 13,
the day Dad transported the guns,

314
00:24:15,859 --> 00:24:17,527
the deal went awry.

315
00:24:18,962 --> 00:24:22,933
So, the factory manager turned
to Sasaoka of the Prefectural Police.

316
00:24:24,568 --> 00:24:25,569
At the time,

317
00:24:26,503 --> 00:24:30,273
Sasaoka and the Igarashi-gumi
were busy with evictions.

318
00:24:31,141 --> 00:24:33,843
Mogi's shop was caught up in that.

319
00:24:34,878 --> 00:24:40,884
Sasaoka talked to the Igarashi-gumi
to get them to spare Mogi.

320
00:24:41,785 --> 00:24:43,253
Wait a minute.

321
00:24:43,320 --> 00:24:45,855
The gun deal and the eviction cases
are unrelated, right?

322
00:24:46,423 --> 00:24:47,724
It was an exchange.

323
00:24:49,259 --> 00:24:53,496
In exchange for stopping
the eviction, the son…

324
00:24:54,898 --> 00:24:57,400
had to help "tidy up" the messy gun deal.

325
00:25:02,505 --> 00:25:03,506
The son?

326
00:25:05,008 --> 00:25:06,042
We know him as…

327
00:25:09,879 --> 00:25:11,114
Mogi.

328
00:25:19,356 --> 00:25:20,991
Tidying up the mess…

329
00:25:23,960 --> 00:25:25,228
What exactly did he do?

330
00:25:31,167 --> 00:25:33,336
"Get rid of that family."

331
00:25:38,642 --> 00:25:39,776
And, probably…

332
00:25:42,112 --> 00:25:43,747
They meant our family.

333
00:25:53,256 --> 00:25:55,091
-Minoru.
-It's just speculation.

334
00:25:55,158 --> 00:25:57,160
That's why we must investigate.

335
00:25:57,761 --> 00:25:58,662
Investigate what?

336
00:26:00,296 --> 00:26:01,765
Will you investigate Mogi?

337
00:26:01,831 --> 00:26:04,534
The tatami shop owner
refused the eviction and was killed.

338
00:26:05,268 --> 00:26:08,171
-Mogi's mom must've been targeted too.
-Wait a minute.

339
00:26:08,972 --> 00:26:10,607
This is Mogi we're talking about.

340
00:26:11,408 --> 00:26:13,176
There's no way he could do that.

341
00:26:13,677 --> 00:26:15,211
Besides, Mogi has an alibi.

342
00:26:15,879 --> 00:26:18,348
<i>He was caught up in the fire</i>
<i>at the factory.</i>

343
00:26:18,415 --> 00:26:19,949
He was burned, you know that too!

344
00:26:20,016 --> 00:26:20,684
I know.

345
00:26:20,750 --> 00:26:22,385
-Then…
-But!

346
00:26:23,820 --> 00:26:26,156
That's what Tsuda's notebook says.

347
00:26:30,393 --> 00:26:31,327
Then…

348
00:26:33,329 --> 00:26:35,532
Are you saying Mogi is lying?

349
00:26:42,539 --> 00:26:44,107
Say something.

350
00:26:46,976 --> 00:26:49,145
Do you trust Tsuda more than Mogi?

351
00:26:54,384 --> 00:26:55,652
I'm not helping you with this.

352
00:27:13,236 --> 00:27:15,305
Why did you show it to Minoru?

353
00:27:17,774 --> 00:27:20,043
Even if I hid it,
he would find out eventually.

354
00:27:25,081 --> 00:27:26,116
But…

355
00:27:27,350 --> 00:27:29,152
I guess it really was a mistake.

356
00:27:30,954 --> 00:27:33,323
All I did was make Minoru
suffer even more.

357
00:27:34,390 --> 00:27:37,927
Minoru has always been attached to Mogi.

358
00:27:39,662 --> 00:27:42,432
When he started to understand
what happened to our parents,

359
00:27:43,666 --> 00:27:46,069
there was a time
when he wouldn't talk to anyone.

360
00:27:48,404 --> 00:27:49,272
But…

361
00:27:50,373 --> 00:27:52,242
Mogi was the only exception.

362
00:27:54,611 --> 00:27:57,981
<i>The food he made</i>
<i>tasted exactly like Mom's.</i>

363
00:27:59,682 --> 00:28:00,650
<i>That's why,</i>

364
00:28:02,585 --> 00:28:04,420
I guess it made him feel safe.

365
00:28:05,755 --> 00:28:09,559
When you're with him, you can forget
about a lot of things, right?

366
00:28:12,762 --> 00:28:14,264
It's the same for me too.

367
00:28:17,333 --> 00:28:18,968
In front of Mogi, I could…

368
00:28:21,304 --> 00:28:23,473
smile sincerely, just like the old days.

369
00:28:27,944 --> 00:28:29,946
Are you going to continue anyway?

370
00:28:34,284 --> 00:28:36,119
Even if it means more pain?

371
00:28:51,901 --> 00:28:55,138
MOGI FROM THE CHINESE SHOP
RODE OUT ON A BICYCLE

372
00:29:26,903 --> 00:29:28,004
What's wrong?

373
00:29:29,939 --> 00:29:34,077
The stove at the shop wasn't working well,
so I had some leftover ingredients.

374
00:29:34,711 --> 00:29:36,479
So that's why you closed the shop.

375
00:29:37,547 --> 00:29:39,482
I'm borrowing the kitchen.

376
00:29:48,358 --> 00:29:49,492
I'll help.

377
00:29:50,126 --> 00:29:52,729
This feels kind of nostalgic.

378
00:29:55,465 --> 00:29:56,466
A long time ago,

379
00:29:56,532 --> 00:29:59,002
you brought a stool
into the shop's kitchen

380
00:29:59,068 --> 00:30:00,303
and helped me, remember?

381
00:30:01,871 --> 00:30:03,873
Because I wanted to learn how to cook.

382
00:30:05,575 --> 00:30:09,178
In that kitchen,
we used to talk about all kinds of things.

383
00:30:10,346 --> 00:30:11,848
Like badmouthing customers.

384
00:30:13,983 --> 00:30:15,118
That's right.

385
00:30:20,089 --> 00:30:21,057
Hey, Mogi.

386
00:30:21,124 --> 00:30:22,091
Yes?

387
00:30:26,496 --> 00:30:28,665
Is there something you need to tell me?

388
00:30:33,336 --> 00:30:34,203
Huh?

389
00:30:42,745 --> 00:30:44,080
No, not really.

390
00:30:48,785 --> 00:30:49,819
I see.

391
00:30:53,690 --> 00:30:55,191
Forget I asked.

392
00:30:57,160 --> 00:30:58,061
Okay.

393
00:31:00,797 --> 00:31:01,631
Any quail eggs?

394
00:31:02,298 --> 00:31:03,132
Oh, wait.

395
00:31:03,666 --> 00:31:05,668
I might have forgotten them.

396
00:31:05,735 --> 00:31:07,470
I'll go buy some.

397
00:31:08,404 --> 00:31:10,139
Or Makoto won't shut up about it.

398
00:31:11,307 --> 00:31:12,575
Sorry.

399
00:32:06,629 --> 00:32:08,231
TAGUSARI HOUSE

400
00:32:14,771 --> 00:32:18,307
KARASHIMA METAL FACTORY

401
00:33:20,570 --> 00:33:23,806
I think they already know.

402
00:33:27,176 --> 00:33:29,278
Makoto and Minoru…

403
00:33:35,351 --> 00:33:39,155
The next time I see them, they'll surely…

404
00:33:50,967 --> 00:33:52,435
It's all over for me!

405
00:33:59,675 --> 00:34:02,311
It's from over 30 years ago, you know.

406
00:34:04,881 --> 00:34:07,350
Hardly any records remain.

407
00:34:08,751 --> 00:34:10,319
There's no way they know.

408
00:34:16,926 --> 00:34:18,060
It's okay.

409
00:34:20,363 --> 00:34:22,965
Everyone will continue to be happy.

410
00:35:06,008 --> 00:35:07,543
<i>The day of the factory fire,</i>

411
00:35:07,610 --> 00:35:12,081
Mogi, who had come to cook,
went to get a fire extinguisher,

412
00:35:12,148 --> 00:35:14,550
<i>then lost consciousness and got burned.</i>

413
00:35:14,617 --> 00:35:15,985
1995, APRIL 26

414
00:35:17,420 --> 00:35:20,890
But the only ones
who could vouch for his actions

415
00:35:20,957 --> 00:35:22,658
were Ms. Fumi and the factory manager.

416
00:35:26,462 --> 00:35:30,233
Right after the fire broke out,
Mom and Dad were killed.

417
00:35:31,234 --> 00:35:33,336
If he ran from our house to the factory,

418
00:35:33,402 --> 00:35:35,671
he could make it back
before the fire department arrives.

419
00:35:48,851 --> 00:35:51,687
It seems the factory
used to store unshipped aluminum,

420
00:35:51,754 --> 00:35:54,257
and zinc scraps.

421
00:35:55,791 --> 00:35:59,128
According to reports, they were blown
everywhere by the explosion.

422
00:36:11,607 --> 00:36:12,808
Mogi…

423
00:36:14,844 --> 00:36:17,046
should have metal burns.

424
00:36:20,082 --> 00:36:21,517
If he was in the factory,

425
00:36:21,584 --> 00:36:25,054
he must have been burned
by scattered metal fragments.

426
00:36:28,691 --> 00:36:33,829
Metal burns reach the dermis,
so the scars never completely disappear.

427
00:36:35,931 --> 00:36:38,768
BURN SCARS ON THE BACK

428
00:36:38,834 --> 00:36:40,269
Even now,

429
00:36:40,903 --> 00:36:44,006
there should be white scars
left scattered on his body.

430
00:36:45,875 --> 00:36:49,612
If those scars aren't there, it means
he wasn't burned in the factory fire,

431
00:36:50,379 --> 00:36:52,081
but by another reason.

432
00:36:53,683 --> 00:36:54,884
For example,

433
00:36:56,152 --> 00:36:57,620
where he was before the fire.

434
00:36:58,788 --> 00:37:00,022
What has gotten into you?

435
00:37:03,959 --> 00:37:06,162
It would mean Mogi was lying.

436
00:37:21,010 --> 00:37:23,112
Dad's gun is missing.

437
00:37:23,179 --> 00:37:25,214
It was still there this morning.

438
00:37:32,488 --> 00:37:33,956
Shall we go check?

439
00:37:40,496 --> 00:37:43,499
If his body has scattered
white burn marks,

440
00:37:46,736 --> 00:37:48,437
he's not the culprit.

441
00:38:05,388 --> 00:38:06,756
Are you closing already?

442
00:38:09,558 --> 00:38:10,693
Yes.

443
00:38:11,460 --> 00:38:14,230
There are no customers,
so I thought I might as well.

444
00:38:14,797 --> 00:38:17,833
In that case, want to go to a public bath?

445
00:38:18,868 --> 00:38:19,902
A public bath?

446
00:38:25,908 --> 00:38:28,177
Been a long time since I've been here.

447
00:38:28,978 --> 00:38:30,813
It's still the same old lady.

448
00:38:33,849 --> 00:38:35,117
Welcome.

449
00:38:35,718 --> 00:38:37,853
-Ma'am.
-Yes?

450
00:38:37,920 --> 00:38:40,322
-For three people…
-No, it's fine.

451
00:38:40,389 --> 00:38:41,524
I invited you.

452
00:38:42,057 --> 00:38:43,159
I'll pay.

453
00:38:52,101 --> 00:38:53,636
Okay, thank you.

454
00:38:59,442 --> 00:39:01,544
Does it look different inside?

455
00:39:02,778 --> 00:39:04,513
The Mount Fuji painting was redone.

456
00:39:52,428 --> 00:39:53,362
What's wrong?

457
00:40:01,103 --> 00:40:02,171
Mogi.

458
00:40:09,111 --> 00:40:10,246
You've gotten old.

459
00:40:26,028 --> 00:40:28,964
You guys will end up
like this too, someday.

460
00:40:36,972 --> 00:40:38,140
I feel…

461
00:40:40,209 --> 00:40:41,477
kind of happy.

462
00:40:46,115 --> 00:40:48,150
To take a bath

463
00:40:49,652 --> 00:40:51,587
with you two, Makoto and Minoru.

464
00:40:54,490 --> 00:40:56,225
We've known each other a long time,

465
00:40:58,360 --> 00:40:59,662
but we've never done this.

466
00:41:03,032 --> 00:41:04,099
Right.

467
00:41:10,706 --> 00:41:12,207
It really has…

468
00:41:17,880 --> 00:41:19,448
been a long time.

469
00:42:07,096 --> 00:42:10,633
FROM: YUKITERU MOGI
TO: MINORU TAGUSARI

470
00:42:17,606 --> 00:42:19,008
Mr. Tagusari.

471
00:42:20,909 --> 00:42:22,044
Mr. Tagusari?

472
00:42:23,178 --> 00:42:26,048
A male body in Kanazawa Ward,
suspected foul play.

473
00:42:26,115 --> 00:42:27,182
Okay.

474
00:42:57,446 --> 00:43:00,716
The deceased is Yukiteru Mogi,
61 years old.

475
00:43:26,508 --> 00:43:27,443
Mogi?

476
00:43:38,253 --> 00:43:41,657
<i>Please don't hurt my brother any further.</i>

477
00:43:41,724 --> 00:43:43,325
<i>Was it all a lie?</i>

478
00:43:43,392 --> 00:43:45,561
How does he intend to end this?

479
00:43:45,627 --> 00:43:48,197
Why do you think we joined the police?

480
00:43:48,263 --> 00:43:49,231
Subtitle translation by: Nix S.

